     ssssttttaaaaggggeeeeiiiinnnniiiitttt tells stgdaemon to drain the service, i.e. rejects
     new  stage  requests but let the current ones complete; then
     reread the pool configuration file:   some  pools  may  have
     been  added  or  suppressed or filesystems in pools may have
     been added or removed; then adjust space information accord-
     ing  to  the  new  configuration  and  restart  the service.
